 {"id":"ft-3681t","title":"[program][epic] Native FrankenTerm Convergence: NTM Superset + Connector Fabric","description":"# Program: FrankenTerm Native Convergence (NTM Superset + Flywheel Connector Fabric)

## Background
This program captures a full replacement strategy for `/dp/ntm` capabilities inside FrankenTerm's native mux/control plane, while deeply integrating `/dp/flywheel_connectors` so FrankenTerm can orchestrate and react to external systems as a first-class swarm platform.

## Intent
No incremental half-measures. The target state is a decisive platform shift where FrankenTerm natively owns orchestration, policy, workflow automation, connector execution, and operational observability.

## Scope Boundaries
- In-scope: command/control parity with NTM, deliberate supersets that exploit native mux internals, connector mesh integration, security model unification, migration/cutover.
- Out-of-scope: preserving tmux-oriented architecture assumptions as a long-term dependency.

## Strategic Outcome
A single native platform where operator workflows, agent swarms, and connector automation are cohesive, policy-governed, and measurable.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Every NTM capability domain has an explicit FrankenTerm-native replacement path.
2. Flywheel connector primitives are integrated as first-class control-plane capabilities (not bolt-ons).
3. Program plan includes dependency order, validation gates, migration path, and rollback controls.
4. Program completion criteria are measurable with performance/reliability/security outcomes.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-02T19:09:40.149033Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-02T19:09:40.536482Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","fcp-integration","native-mux","ntm-convergence","program"]}
